Proud of myself this weekend, except I could have done better today (I'll explain below):Yesterday had the potential to be a disaster because we went over our friends' house for D&D and board games. I made sure we ate lunch before we left the house, and emailed my friend and asked what they were planning for dinner and if she would like to try the new recipe I found for enchilada pie (which meant I could control what went into it and how big portion sizes were). She was game, so I ended up cooking it at her house. I also brought some Jello temptations snacks with me because I figured, while they are fairly healthy eaters, there were likely to be chips around, and it's WAY easier to overeat on a bag of chips than it is on a finite amount of pudding snack. I ended up having some chips, but limited myself to a single serving, and also treated myself to a cider. Result? I stayed within my calories for the day. Today was not as successful, but not for the reason you'd think. We got up late (that always throws my day off), and ate "brunch", and then didn't really eat again until around 7:30-8pm. Result: I ate a lot of food around and after dinner (kiwi wrapped in salami was the star of the show ) to attempt to get into the calorie range for today, feel ill now, and still ate way fewer calories than I should have (just above 1000, with a target range of 1570-1920). I've got my lunch all packed for tomorrow, anyway, and made baked apple cinnamon walnut oatmeal for breakfast for the next few days, so at least that's all set. I've also planned out dinner tomorrow.So all in all, not a disastrous weekend by any means, but I wish I planned more for today so I could have been within my target range.
