I always enjoy reading about actors who have to stay in great shape, particularly when they are honest about the trials and tribulations they go through. One that has always stuck with me was reading an article about Jamie Bamber (Apollo on Battlestar Galactica). He talks about how he doesn't like running on a treadmill, what works for him, what doesn't, and how he motivates himself. I particularly like the part where he talks about how he loves food. The main takeaway I got from it is that he found a happy medium where he enjoys getting fitter, and he enjoys getting fatter. To him, it's about finding that leeway that he can work within, so he knows when he can relax and eat hamburgers and enjoy it, and he knows when he needs to hit the running trails and enjoy that as well.I still have about 20 lbs to lose, but instead of having a target weight, I'm going to go with the bamber method, and instead have a target weight range, where once I hit the bottom of the range, I can relax, then when I hit the top of the range, it's time to crack down again. And learn to enjoy that moderate swing.
